Consulting service agreements are documents used when an individual or company hires an outside consultant for their expertise. Consultants work in multiple fields including the medical, engineering and human resources fields, and present expert opinions on the current conditions of their client's business.The contracts define the scope of the work the consultant will perform and outline the terms of their payment. These agreements also cover the method of payment and the estimated time for the project. Consulting service agreements may contain clauses that outline terms and conditions regarding the consultation, and will make the parties aware of any repercussions that may arise due to breach of contract.There are several varieties of consulting work, and a contract may contain language specific to a certain type. Contracts may include clauses regarding ownership of the work product, such as reports and case studies. Using a consultant services agreement helps a consultant see what the client expects.        



